div.bibl: Svenska Tribunen, Feb. 20, 1901. SWEDISH AMERICAN WOMEN'S CLUB.

body.p: p.11.... The Swedish American Women's Club held their annual meeting on Wednesday, Feb. 13th, at Mrs. Martha Hall's Home at 1762 N. Clark St. About seventy women were present. Dr. Francis Dickenson, President of Harvey Medical School who was guest of honor spoke on "Women in Public Life."

As officers for the year, those elected are: Othelia Myhrman, President; Miss Lottie Forstrom, Vice President; Mrs. Martha S. Hall, Recording Secretary; Miss Amanda Lundquist, Corresponding Secretary; Mrs. Hulia Johnson, Collector of Dues.
After the meeting coffee and Swedish coffee-cake was served.
